				\begin{document}$$\Delta G_{\mathrm{light}}(X_{\mathrm{Br}},T) = \Delta G_{\mathrm{dark}}(X_{\mathrm{Br}},T) + \frac{4}{3}\pi r^3 \cdot \Delta g_{\mathrm{s}}(X_{\mathrm{Br}})$$\end{document}When Δgs becomes sufficiently large, the strain energy would be released by de-mixing the halogen anions and forming Br- and I-rich domains (i.e. phase separation).
